## Recruiting participants

You must [include people with disabilities at every stage of testing](/user-research/accessibility). 

Do not only do an accessibility testing sprint at the end of the project or just before your assessment.

You can choose from a number of options for how to recruit participants from outside DfE (sometimes called external research). Make sure you choose the most appropriate method for your project.

You can choose to:

- contact existing participants
- use recruitment agencies
- ask schools or charities you have an existing relationship with

You cannot use social media to recruit participants. 

Additional <a href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1kmx7aiSPIZELKEQ0-csYRl38fATHmPGArkZ1xaR8iNY" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">guidance on recruiting participants from outside DfE (Google Document)</a>

## If you're finding it difficult to recruit participants with access needs

